<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-01-24T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-01-24T15:00:00-05:00" n="149" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">399.10–<gloss target="#t_UPU1">UPU</gloss>/1–2451: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Brazil</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                                </gloss>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-01-24T15:00:00-05:00">January
                                    24, 1951—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>507. Ref <gloss target="#t_Depcirtel1">Depcirtel</gloss> 384 Jan 15 and
                                <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 929 Jan 18.<note n="1" xml:id="d149fn1">Telegram 929 not printed.</note>
                            <gloss target="#t_USRep1">USRep</gloss>
                            <gloss target="#t_UPU1">UPU</gloss> Conference Cairo informs <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> vote on US proposal re Chi
                            representation as well as Sov motion seat Chi Commie will be taken at
                            morning session Jan 25. No Del has been willing second US proposal,
                            although Arg Rep will speak in favor. Braz Rep has indicated <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> he instructed vote for US proposal
                            but not speak on subj and construes this mean he cannot second US
                            motion. Since situation precarious, request you in your discretion ask
                                <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> urgently instruct Braz Rep
                            second and speak in favor US motion.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>